China reiterated its "one country, two systems" approach to Taiwan while introducing an anti-secession law.
The Republic of China's officials in the US will monitor developments closely.
The Mainland Affairs Council will watch China's communication with the US regarding the law.
Taiwan strongly opposes Beijing's move, calling it a threat to regional stability.
President Chen warned of Beijing's psychological warfare tactics.
The US and EU view China's law as counterproductive.
Taiwan plans to counteract the law through legislative resolutions.
Overall, tensions between Taiwan and mainland China are escalating due to the proposed anti-secession law.
